race.comment: WHAT A FLIRT (9) finds it hard to win with two victories from 21 starts. Again tasted defeat last start when fifth over 1400m at Casterton, beaten 1.5 lengths. Finds an easier assignment and can get the job done. BOULDER JACK (1) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 1.1 lengths when fifth over 1400m at Echuca four weeks ago after being in the firing line on the bend. Nicely placed to get the prize. SNATCHED (12) settled well back from a good draw last time before getting home nicely to finish fifth, beaten 5 lengths, over 1110m at Kilmore. Warrants plenty of respect. ARTPARK (5) mixes form but can produce, namely two starts ago when winning at Warrnambool.
